Shawn Leas wrote:
>bindkey -s "^[OA" "^[ka"
>bindkey -s "^[OB" "^[ja"
>bindkey -s "^[OD" "^[ha"
>bindkey -s "^[OC" "^[la"

That's a terminal issue.  Some terminals send "^[OA" instead of "^[[A".
Of course, a lot of terminals send sequences completely different from
these, but zsh should probably recognise both of these sets by default.

